claim.claim-text:
1. A method for dynamically scheduling communications to a plurality of receivers over a TDMA channel that is partitioned into frames each consisting of slots, comprising the steps of: 
measuring a channel condition of each receiver; 
dividing the receivers into receiver groups according their channel conditions; 
partitioning the TDMA channel into a recurring sequence of slots; 
dividing each sequence into a certain number of slot groups; and 
allocating the slot groups to the receiver groups according to the receivers' channel conditions.
